  1. Oxford 3000
  2. Oxford 09

Words 801-900

  1. dream
    She had a dream about flying over the mountains.

  2. dress
    She wore a beautiful dress to the party.

  3. dressed
    He was dressed in a suit for the meeting.

  4. drink
    Can I have a drink of water, please?

  5. drive
    He learned to drive when he was eighteen.

  6. driver
    The driver stopped the car at the red light.

  7. driving
    Driving in the city can be stressful.

  8. drop
    Be careful not to drop the glass.

  9. drug
    The doctor gave her a drug to help with the pain.

  10. drum
    He played the drum in the school band.

  11. drunk
    He felt sick because he had drunk too much juice.

  12. dry
    The clothes are dry now after hanging in the sun.

  13. due
    The train is due to arrive at 5 PM.

  14. during
    She stayed quiet during the meeting.

  15. dust
    There was a layer of dust on the old table.

  16. duty
    It is our duty to help those in need.

  17. DVD
    They watched a movie on DVD last night.

  18. each
    Each student received a book.

  19. ear
    She whispered something in his ear.

  20. early
    He arrived early to get a good seat.

  21. earn
    She works hard to earn her salary.

  22. earth
    The earth is round and full of life.

  23. earthquake
    The earthquake caused damage to many buildings.

  24. easily
    She solved the problem easily.

  25. east
    The sun rises in the east.

  26. eastern
    They visited the eastern part of the country.

  27. easy
    This question is easy to answer.

  28. eat
    They like to eat fresh fruit every morning.

  29. economic
    The country is facing economic challenges.

  30. economy
    Tourism is important for the local economy.

  31. edge
    He stood at the edge of the cliff.

  32. edit
    She will edit the document before sending it.

  33. edition
    This is the latest edition of the book.

  34. editor
    The editor reviewed the article carefully.

  35. educate
    Schools aim to educate children for the future.

  36. educated
    He is well-educated and speaks several languages.

  37. education
    Education is important for personal growth.

  38. educational
    The trip was both fun and educational.

  39. effect
    The new law had a positive effect on the community.

  40. effective
    This medicine is very effective for headaches.

  41. effectively
    She managed the team effectively.

  42. efficient
    The new system is more efficient than the old one.

  43. effort
    He made an effort to finish the project on time.

  44. egg
    She boiled an egg for breakfast.

  45. eight
    There are eight apples in the basket.

  46. eighteen
    She turned eighteen last week.

  47. eighty
    The book costs eighty dollars.

  48. either
    You can choose either tea or coffee.

  49. elderly
    The elderly man walked slowly with a cane.

  50. elect
    They will elect a new president next year.

  51. election
    The election results will be announced tomorrow.

  52. electric
    The car runs on electric power.

  53. electrical
    He fixed the electrical problem in the house.

  54. electricity
    The storm caused a loss of electricity in the area.

  55. electronic
    She bought an electronic device for her studies.

  56. element
    Water is an important element for life.

  57. elephant
    The elephant is the largest land animal.

  58. eleven
    The meeting starts at eleven o’clock.

  59. else
    Is there anything else you need?

  60. elsewhere
    If we can’t find it here, we will look elsewhere.

  61. email
    She sent an email to her teacher.

  62. embarrassed
    He felt embarrassed when he forgot her name.

  63. embarrassing
    It was an embarrassing moment for everyone.

  64. emerge
    The sun began to emerge from behind the clouds.

  65. emergency
    Call this number in case of an emergency.

  66. emotion
    She couldn’t hide her emotion during the speech.

  67. emotional
    It was an emotional day for the family.

  68. emphasis
    The teacher placed emphasis on the importance of reading.

  69. emphasize
    He tried to emphasize the need for teamwork.

  70. employ
    The company plans to employ more workers.

  71. employee
    Each employee received a bonus this year.

  72. employer
    The employer provided good benefits for the staff.

  73. employment
    She is looking for employment in the city.

  74. empty
    The box was empty when they opened it.

  75. enable
    This software will enable you to edit photos easily.

  76. encounter
    They had a strange encounter in the forest.

  77. encourage
    The teacher tried to encourage the students to ask questions.

  78. end
    The movie had a happy end.

  79. ending
    The book’s ending was unexpected.

  80. enemy
    They worked together to defeat the enemy.

  81. energy
    She has a lot of energy in the morning.

  82. engage
    The speaker tried to engage the audience with questions.

  83. engaged
    They got engaged last summer.

  84. engine
    The car’s engine needs to be repaired.

  85. engineer
    The engineer designed a new bridge.

  86. engineering
    She is studying engineering at university.

  87. enhance
    The new features will enhance the user experience.

  88. enjoy
    They enjoy spending time with their friends.

  89. enormous
    The elephant is an enormous animal.

  90. enough
    There is enough food for everyone.

  91. enquiry
    She made an enquiry about the course.

  92. ensure
    Please ensure that the door is locked before you leave.

  93. enter
    You need a key to enter the building.

  94. entertain
    The magician will entertain the children at the party.

  95. entertainment
    The city offers a variety of entertainment options.

  96. enthusiasm
    She showed great enthusiasm for the project.

  97. enthusiastic
    The students were enthusiastic about the trip.

  98. entire
    He spent the entire day working on the report.

  99. entirely
    The story is entirely true.

  100. entrance
    The entrance to the park is on the left.
